Rating: 2
Made this for a dinner party last night on a sweltering summer evening. Everyone seemed to like it--used a Trinidadian hot sauce (with a mango base) and substituted veg broth for chicken b/c I had vegetarians coming over. I liked the soup, though it was a little thick. Best served in small dishes, as an appetizer. I only used 2 of the 4 avocados---any more and it would have been as thick as guacamole.

Rating: 2
This recipe is a good start but definitely needs work to make it better. First, there is too much chicken broth - it is better with about 1/2 as much broth and the rest replaced with water, otherwise its taste overpowers the very delicate taste of the avocado. More importantly, it contains a large amount of fat and the recipe calls for no acid to balance it. I added the juice of a whole lemon and some sherry vinegar to balance the fat. Some of the other reviewers who commented it was bland and that adding more hot pepper sauce did not fix it were I am sure experiencing this problem. So with some acid to brighten the flavor and balance the richness of the avocado and milk, its pretty good.

Rating: 4
Addendum.... after my company really raved about this soup. I skipped the chicken stock and used chicken boullion with a tiny bit of water. I used a finishing salt and I loaded in the sherry. I also added some toasted sesame seeds as a garnish with parmesan cheese. All of these things really boosted the already wonderful flavors of this fun recipe. Not sure where others had problem with this nutritional summer soup. Additionally, I used lactose free skim milk. This choice kept it light and summery.

